# Exceptions Assignment

## Description
This Java assignment practices ArrayList, generics, casting, and exception handling.

## File
- Exceptions.java

## What the program does
- Creates an ArrayList with Strings and Integers
- Tries to cast each item to Integer
- Uses try/catch to handle ClassCastException
- Prints the error, index, and value
- Continues running after errors

## How to Run
1. Open Eclipse
2. Create a Java Project named ExceptionsAssignment
3. Create a class named Exceptions
4. Paste the code
5. Run Exceptions.java

## Expected Output
Some values will cause errors because they are Strings, not Integers.
The Integer value 48 will be cast successfully.